<div class="headCo">

# <span>Recording / MIDI In</span>

<div class="headCo_co">

<div>

<div class="infobloc">

<div class="txt">

Some score editors allow the recording of MIDI keybord or other incoming
note events.

</div>

<div class="txtRes">

<table>
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 50%" />
<col style="width: 50%" />
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr class="odd">
<td><div class="dk_txtRes_txt txt">
<p>Use the "RECORD" button of the playing palette: all incoming events will be recorded untill "STOP" is pressed.</p>
<p>The corresponding notes should then appear in the score editor and are stored in the corresponding box.</p>
</div></td>
<td><div class="caption">
<div class="caption_co">
<img src="../res/midi-rec.png" width="300" height="89" alt="midi-rec.png" />
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

</div>

</div>

<div class="bloc complement">

<div class="bloc_ti complement_ti">

<span>Input MIDI Port</span>

</div>

<div class="txt">

The input MIDI port number can be changed in the OM `MIDI` Preferences
tab.

The MidiShare Setup panel allows to control the connection of the
different output and input port to external devices (e.g. keyboards,
etc.).

</div>

<div class="linkSet">

<div class="linkSet_ti">

<span>Setting MIDI Ports</span>

</div>

<div class="linkUL">

  - [<span>Managing MIDI Ports</span>](MIDI-Ports.md)

</div>

</div>

</div>

</div>

